jgrasstools standalone mode
===========================

To run a jgrasstools script (oms3) from commandline, simply
run the script for your operating system passing it the
jgrasstools script (oms3) as argument.

Syntax
======
LINUX: ./jgrasstools.sh path/to/your/script.oms
MACOSX: same as linux
WINDOWS: jgrasstools.bat path\to\your\script.oms


DEDICATED MEMORY
================
The memeory dedicated to the process is defined in the jgrasstools 
script (.sh for linux and macosx, .bat for windows). By default
it is set to 2 gigabytes.
To change the value simply change the -Xmx2g part.
Examples:
500 mega: -Xmx500m
4 giga: -Xmx4g

